- non-commercial internal use;
- open-source projects that do not sell or host @better-grid/pro as part of a
  paid product or service.

2. Commercial production use

Commercial production use requires a valid Better Grid Pro license from the
Better Grid project owner.

Commercial production use includes use by or for a business, paid product,
paid service, client project, internal business application, SaaS product, or
any other revenue-generating or business-operational context.

3. What you may not do

Without written permission, you may not:

- sell, sublicense, rent, lease, or commercially redistribute @better-grid/pro
  as a standalone library;
- remove or obscure copyright, license, or attribution notices;
- use @better-grid/pro to build a substantially similar data-grid library,
  component library, or plugin package for redistribution;
- offer @better-grid/pro as a hosted service or managed platform whose primary
  purpose is to provide data-grid functionality to third parties.

4. Source availability

The source code is made available for transparency, evaluation, learning,
debugging, and easier integration. Source availability does not grant MIT,
Apache, GPL, or other open-source rights to @better-grid/pro.

5. No hard runtime enforcement

@better-grid/pro may run without a license key. That does not waive the
commercial license requirement for commercial production use.

